ved social assistance and access to birth control. Yet progress was uneven and even the movement itself was marked by class and racial inequities. We Shall Persist captures both the long campaign and the years of disappointment. Suffrage victories across Atlantic Canada were steps in an unfinished march toward full gender, race, and class equality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSuffragezAtlantic ProvincesxHistory. 0aSuffragistszAtlantic ProvincesxHistory. 0aVotingzAtlantic ProvincesxHistory. 0aWomenxLegal status, laws, etc.zAtlantic ProvincesxHistory. 0aWomenxSuffragezAtlantic ProvincesxHistory. 0aWomenxSuffragezCanadaxHistory. 0aWomenzAtlantic ProvincesxSocial conditions. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Provincial, Territorial & Local / Atlantic Provinces (NB, NL, NS, PE).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packagez978311143542808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311140824840uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486319340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774863193423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774863193/original  a978-3-11-127195-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-140824-8  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-143542-8  ACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packageb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles